Government Orders: - The Assistant Group Development Officer in the Maharashtra Development Service, Group-B cadre (Pay Level S-15: 41800-132300) has been given ad-hoc promotion under the orders of the Group Development Officer, Group-A cadre (Pay Level S-20: 56100-177500) read here. Out of these promoted officers, the officers mentioned in the table below have been promoted in front of their names on the recommendation of the Civil Services Board and with the approval of the competent authority by posting the same in column No. The post is being replaced as specified in Section 3: -

2. The concerned Divisional Commissioner / CEO, Zila Parishad shall immediately relieve the above mentioned officers posted in Group-A cadre as Block Development Officers and instruct them to appear at the place of new appointment.

3. Group Development Officer, Read in Group-A Cadre The above officers, who have been given ad-hoc promotion under the order herein, should immediately join the place of their new appointment and submit a compliance report to the Government after assuming charge of the said post. The officer concerned should not go on unauthorised leave. Their attention is being drawn to the circular of the General Administration Department No: CDR 1082/2567/28 Eleven, dated 30.8.1982. They should note that in view of the instructions contained therein, they will be liable for disciplinary action if they submit any form of application for cancellation of appointment.
By order of the Governor of Maharashtra]
